CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 17 reads: "Workers Relax - Voting was light in most districts and plenty of time was available during the day for relaxation as this group of poll workers was found doing. One of the lightest turnouts in district history occurred."
TitMainTitle: Group of poll workers, including man wearing overalls, and four women, one holding soda bottle, next to table with papers, one inscribed "Democratic Primary Ballot," in interior with brick wall and bulletin board during 1955 primary elections
